data.enText: a member of an ancient race of people living in what is now Israel and Palestine. Their writings and traditions form the basis of the Jewish religion.
the language traditionally used by the Hebrew people

data.chText: 现代希伯来语（现代以色列的官方语言）
data.enText: a modern form of the Hebrew language which is the official language of modern Israel

means: 现代希伯来语(现代以色列的官方语言)

value.def: Hebrew is a language that was spoken by Jews in former times. A modern form of Hebrew is spoken now in Israel.

example.ex: He is a fluent speaker of Hebrew.
example.tran: 他说一口流利的希伯来语。

value.def: In former times, a Hebrew was a Jewish person.

example.ex: ...the exodus of the Hebrews from Egypt.

value.tran: 希伯来人（旧时指犹太人）

value.def: Hebrew means belonging to or relating to the Hebrew language or people.

example.tran: 受到尊崇的希伯来语报纸《国土报》

example.ex: He sits puzzling over ancient Hebrew texts.
example.tran: 他坐在那里对着古老的希伯来文本大伤脑筋。

value.tran: 希伯来语的;希伯来人的
